Package: iDOM
Title: Analysis Tools of Dissolved Organic Matter Characterized by High-Resolution Mass Spectrometry
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Jianjun", "Wang", email = "jjwang@niglas.ac.cn", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(URL = "https://jjwang.name/")),
    person("Ang", "Hu", role = "aut"),
    person("Fanfan", "Meng", role = "aut")
  )
Description: Provides tools for basic and advanced statistical analyses and visualization of dissolved organic matter (DOM) characterized by
    Fourier transform ion cyclotron resonance mass spectrometry (FT-ICR MS). 
    Supports analyses of molecular composition, molecular traits, molecular transformations, diversity, dendrogram structure, assembly
    processes, environmental responses, and DOM-microbe associations, and can integrate environmental and microbial data to explore
    abiotic and biotic drivers of DOM variation, as described in Meng et al. (2025) <doi:10.1002/mlf2.70002>. 
    The 'molTrait()' function conditionally uses the suggested package 'ftmsRanalysis' for FT-MS data preprocessing; it is available from
    <https://github.com/EMSL-Computing/ftmsRanalysis>.
